[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMS: [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ; base unit: [0m[1;36m0000000000000000000000000000000000000000[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mxz[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp57a65_jl[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz_encode_stream -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-use-after-free was detected by AddressSanitizer while running the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fuzz_encode_stream` fuzz target against the XZ library’s LZMA encoder. During a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall to `compute_tree_checksum` in `treeck.c`, memory that had just been freed was [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequently read, leading to an abort.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What the issue is  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  While fuzzing the XZ codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39mspecifically the stream encoder[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreported an illegal [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte read from a freed heap region. The error arises inside [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`src/liblzma/check/treeck.[0m[1;92mc:79[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is invoked via [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`lzma_tree`, `lzma_check_update`, and ultimately the stream encoding path triggered[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the fuzzer entry point [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz_encode_stream.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a classic use-after-free vulnerability: freed heap memory is accessed, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich can lead to undefined behavior, crashes, or potential exploitation.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations and findings  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The bad read occurs [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bytes into a [0m[1;36m56[0m[39m-byte allocation that was already freed. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The allocation happens in `create_tree` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`treeck.[0m[1;92mc:33[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and is freed inside [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`treeck.[0m[1;92mc:90[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A subsequent call to [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` attempts to read from the same memory.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The full call chain:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. fuzz target: `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz_encode_stream.c`  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `fuzz_code` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommon harness[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `lzma_code` → `stream_encode` → `block_encode` → `lzma_check_update` → [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`lzma_tree` → `compute_tree_checksum`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • AddressSanitizer shadow memory indicates the region is marked as freed [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fd`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming the use-after-free.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To understand the full context and potential impact, reviewers should examine:  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `src/liblzma/check/treeck.c` – functions `create_tree`, [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`, and `lzma_tree`  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `src/liblzma/check/check.c` – function `lzma_check_update`  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `src/liblzma/common/block_encoder.c` and `stream_encoder.c` – how checksums are[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated during encoding  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzz harness in `tests/ossfuzz/fuzz_encode_stream.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry into the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblematic code path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReviewing those areas will give a holistic view of the allocation, deallocation, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand subsequent reuse of the checksum tree structure that leads to the [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-use-after-free.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mfuzz_encode_stream[0m                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Create tree node[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:  TreeNode *node = [0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mexit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Configure the node block[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m:  node->value = data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth % len[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:  node->state = STATE_CLEAR;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m:  node->block_width = *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtree_field_t*[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m:  node->block_height = *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtree_field_t*[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata+[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtree_field_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m:  node->block_size = node->block_width * node->block_height;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Decide edge count[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m:  seed = seed * [0m[1;36m31[0m[39m + node->value;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:  node->edge_count = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mseed % [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMAX_EDGES + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:  node->edges = [0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * node->edge_count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!node->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mexit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Build child nodes[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:  for [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < node->edge_count; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[33mi[0m[39m==node->edge_count-[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m && [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnode->[0m[33mblock_size[0m[39m==MAX_BLOCK_WIDTH*MAX_BLOCK_HEIGHT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Max-sized sections must maintain a backlink to the parent[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:      node->edges[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = parent;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:    else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Use offset in seed to choose next depth[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:      size_t next_depth = depth + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mseed % [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmax_depth - depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:      node->edges[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;35mcreate_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata + node->edge_count, len - [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnode->edge_count, next_depth, max_depth, seed + i * [0m[1;36m13[0m[39m, node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:  return node;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/treeck.[0m[1;92mc:66[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m93[0m                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:static uint32_t [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node, unsigned int depth[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Skip if already hashed[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!node || node->state == STATE_HASHED[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Compute initial checksum from depth and value[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:  uint32_t sum = node->value * [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Traverse the child nodes if not already visited[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->state == STATE_CLEAR[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:    node->state = STATE_VISITED;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < node->edge_count; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:      TreeNode *child = node->edges[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchild[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:        sum += [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchild, depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:    node->state = STATE_HASHED;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Free the node and edges[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:  return sum;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/treeck.h:[0m[1;36m11[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m34[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MAX_EDGES [0m[1;36m8[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#define HASH_SEED [0m[1;36m5381[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m13[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m14[0m[39m:#define STATE_CLEAR   [0m[1;36m0[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m15[0m[39m:#define STATE_VISITED [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m16[0m[39m:#define STATE_HASHED  [0m[1;36m2[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m17[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m18[0m[39m:#define MAX_BLOCK_WIDTH  [0m[1;36m0x7fffffff[0m[39mull[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m19[0m[39m:#define MAX_BLOCK_HEIGHT [0m[1;36m0x7fffffff[0m[39mull[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m20[0m[39m:#define TREE_FIELDS [0m[1;36m2[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m:typedef uint32_t tree_field_t;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m23[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m:typedef struct TreeNode [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m:  uint8_t value;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m:  uint64_t block_width;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m:  uint64_t block_height;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:  uint64_t block_size;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:  size_t edge_count;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:  struct TreeNode **edges;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m:  int state;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m for checksum cycle detection[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m TreeNode;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/check.[0m[1;92mc:142[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m150[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m142[0m[39m:    [0m[39mcase LZMA_CHECK_TREE:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mcheck->state.tree = [0m[1;35mlzma_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, size, check->state.tree[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mbreak;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:    [0m[39mdefault:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mbreak;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m150[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Diagnose Root Cause:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The recursive function `compute_tree_checksum` both traverses and frees each [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TreeNode` immediately after processing [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When the tree contains intentional back-links [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcycles[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a recursive re-entry [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon a freed node leads to a use-after-free: the function reads `node->state` from [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed memory and may re-free the same node.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preserve Critical Logic:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must continue to support cycles [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe back-link to `parent`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that maximal[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocks form valid cycles.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The tree checksum algorithm’s state-based cycle-detection [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`state == [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSTATE_VISITED`, `STATE_HASHED`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m must remain intact so that the same node is not [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-counted in the checksum.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The public API [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`lzma_tree` → `compute_tree_checksum`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m must still return the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect “e37vk” checksum of the tree.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must free all allocated memory before returning from `lzma_tree` to avoid [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleaks.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy Overview:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Separate Traversal from Deallocation  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      i. First, traverse the graph, computing the checksum while marking nodes to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoid re-visiting [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas now[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but do *not* free any memory during this phase.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ii. Then, perform a second pass over the same graph [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing the same state [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflags or a fresh visited set[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that frees each node exactly once.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    iii. This two-phase approach prevents any attempt to read or free a node after [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit has already been freed.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Implementation Steps:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Introduce a helper function `static void [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Recursively visits child edges,  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Uses the `state` flags [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor a new flag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to detect and skip already-freed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnodes,  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Frees each node->edges and then node itself.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Modify `compute_tree_checksum` to:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • *Not* call `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Continue to use `state` to detect visited/hashed nodes and compute the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msum without altering the memory layout.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Change `lzma_tree` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe caller of `compute_tree_checksum`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Allocate the tree with `create_tree`,  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Call the revised `compute_tree_checksum` to compute the checksum,  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Immediately after obtaining the checksum, call `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclean up the entire graph,  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Return the computed checksum to the user.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed Steps:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `treeck.c`, before or after existing code, add:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Recursively free all nodes in the tree exactly once[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      static void[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode == NULL || node->state == STATE_HASHED[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          node->state = STATE_HASHED; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m mark as freed[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          for [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < node->edge_count; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Modify `compute_tree_checksum`:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Remove lines [0m[1;36m88[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m90[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      • Keep only traversal and `return sum;`.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Modify the function `lzma_tree` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m98[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m102[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      uint32_t [0m[1;35mlzma_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst uint8_t *data, size_t size, TreeNode *prev[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Existing: create new tree[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          TreeNode *root = [0m[1;35mcreate_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, size, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m[33mmax_depth[0m[39m=*[0m[35m/[0m[95m...[0m[39m, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m*[0m[33mseed[0m[39m=*[0m[35m/[0m[95mHASH_SEED[0m[39m, NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          uint32_t checksum = [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m NEW: free all nodes after checksum[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return checksum;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Ensure that any state flags on recycled trees do not persist across calls: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msince the tree is newly created each `lzma_tree`, using `state = STATE_HASHED` in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`free_tree` has no side-effect on future calls.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification & Side-Effects:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This two-phase approach maintains the existing checksum logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode values, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth weighting, cycle detection[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so numeric outputs remain unchanged.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory is no longer freed mid-traversal; no use-after-free occurs.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A second pass through the tree properly deallocates all nodes exactly once, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoiding leaks or double-frees.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new helper function is internal to `treeck.c` and does not alter public [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPIs or fuzz harnesses.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We avoid touching any fuzzing/harness/test code as required.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add or update any existing unit tests to ensure that `lzma_tree` on small [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgraphs returns the expected checksum and does not leak memory [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., run under ASan[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor Valgrind[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that AddressSanitizer no longer reports use-after-free in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing XZ test suite to ensure no regressions.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References to Similar Patterns:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The two-phase “compute then free” pattern is used elsewhere in the codebase [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor DAG cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee `src/liblzma/common/dag.c` for cleanup helpers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We leverage the same `STATE_HASHED` flag convention to coordinate both [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecksum-phase and free-phase graph visits.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer report of a heap-use-after-free in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` function within `treeck.c` of the liblzma library. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer log shows that `compute_tree_checksum` frees a tree node and then later [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads from that freed memory, leading to a crash.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch attempt was made to remove the premature frees from `compute_tree_checksum`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand defer them to a new `free_tree` helper that recursively frees all nodes after [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe checksum is computed. The patch also updates the `lzma_tree` function to call [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`free_tree` on the root node after producing the checksum.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen this patch was applied, compilation errors arose due to stray line-number [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlabels [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m93[0m[39m:` and `[0m[1;36m95[0m[39m:`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the diff. The errors include “expected ‘;’ after [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpression” and “expected identifier or [0m[32m'[0m[32m([0m[32m'[0m[39m,” indicating incorrect patch [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatting.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer detected a heap-use-after-free in `compute_tree_checksum` at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`treeck.[0m[1;92mc:79:34[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Allocation of a `TreeNode` and its `edges` array in `create_tree`.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Invocation of `[0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` from `lzma_tree`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Inside `compute_tree_checksum`, `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` are [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalled.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The function then returns to its caller, which later attempts to read from the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed node memory, leading to the crash.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer output identifies the freed region and the subsequent invalid read,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming a use-after-free bug.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `compute_tree_checksum`: The two calls `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` were [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoved, with a comment “Memory freed later by [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m”.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A new static function `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was added above `lzma_tree`. It[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperforms a depth-first traversal, frees each node’s `edges` array and the node [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself, and marks nodes as visited via `state == STATE_HASHED`.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `lzma_tree`: After `checksum ^= [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, the code now[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` before returning the checksum.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompilation Log After Patch  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mxz[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp57a65_jl[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz_encode_stream -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a heap-use-after-free detected by AddressSanitizer in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtreeck.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. During checksum computation, the code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed nodes and their edge arrays, but continued to traverse or access them, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleading to invalid reads.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt removed the in-place `free` calls from `compute_tree_checksum`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced a new helper `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to recursively free the entire [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtree exactly once, and added a call to `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` after checksum computation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `lzma_tree`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying this patch, LeakSanitizer reports numerous memory leaks: the root [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnode and all descendant nodes and edge arrays allocated by `create_tree` are never [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed, indicating that `free_tree` is not correctly releasing all allocated memory.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer log shows a UAF at  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `compute_tree_checksum [0m[35m/src/xz/src/liblzma/check/[0m[95mtreeck.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m79:34[0m[39m`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace enters via `lzma_tree` → `lzma_check_update` → `block_encode` → [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`stream_encode` → `lzma_code` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The heap region for a `TreeNode` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m56[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was freed at line [0m[1;36m90[0m[39m of `treeck.c`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand then accessed again [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bytes into that region.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The memory region’s redzone markings [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fd`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m confirm use-after-free.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `compute_tree_checksum` both traverses and deallocates tree nodes, leading to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate inconsistencies and UAF.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No central ownership or proper post-order cleanup exists; nodes may be freed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple times or prematurely.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `compute_tree_checksum`:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Deleted `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Left checksum-only logic in that function.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inserted a new static function in `treeck.c`:  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     static void [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!node || node->state == STATE_HASHED[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         node->state = STATE_HASHED;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         for [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < node->edge_count; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After calling `[0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, added `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe public API [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`lzma_tree` wrapper[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - LeakSanitizer reports:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Direct leak: [0m[1;36m56[0m[39m bytes for the root node [0m[1;39m([0m[39mone allocation via `create_tree`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Indirect leaks: cumulative hundreds of bytes across dozens of child nodes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand their edge arrays.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Every `malloc` in `create_tree` for nodes and edges remains reachable but [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munfreed, indicating `free_tree` did not traverse or free those allocations.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `create_tree` and its allocation patterns: types and counts of node/edge [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocations.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `state` field and its transitions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`STATE_HASHED` vs. other states[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m used [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby both checksum and free routines.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Traversal order in `compute_tree_checksum` vs. `free_tree` to ensure [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpost-order release.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Integration points in `lzma_tree` and `lzma_check_update` to confirm ownership[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand lifecycle of the tree data structure.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential cycles or shared subtrees that could alter free logic or require [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreference counting.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:        sum += [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchild, depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:    node->state = STATE_HASHED;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
