[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mxz[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp57a65_jl[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz_encode_stream -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-use-after-free [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUAF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was detected during fuzz testing of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `lzma_tree` checksum computation in `treeck.c`. The initial log shows that [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` reads from a node after it has been freed, leading to a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash. A patch was introduced that:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added a new `free_tree` helper to recursively free the entire tree after checksum[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputation.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modified `lzma_tree` to call `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` immediately after invoking [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRe-running the fuzzer after applying the patch still produces the same UAF in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`, indicating that the root cause—improper memory management [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside the checksum routine—was not addressed by simply freeing the tree earlier or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlater.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Where it occurs**  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The UAF arises in `compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `src/liblzma/check/treeck.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalled by `lzma_tree`, triggered by fuzz inputs to `fuzz_encode_stream`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Stack trace highlights**  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `compute_tree_checksum` reads [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes from a `TreeNode` that has already been [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The node lived in a [0m[1;36m56[0m[39m-byte heap region [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m0080[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…00b8[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; its shadow bytes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshow the region was marked freed [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fd`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The free happened earlier in the same recursive call to [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`, indicating an internal double-use or premature free.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Key observations**  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The node is freed in `compute_tree_checksum` itself before all its fields or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchild pointers are fully consumed.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `lzma_tree` calls `[0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but does not otherwise [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanage the tree’s memory, relying on `compute_tree_checksum` to deal with node [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifetimes.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The memory was originally allocated by `create_tree` and freed by [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum`, yet access continues afterward.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **treeck.h**  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A new enum state flag `STATE_FREED` was added [0m[1;39m([0m[39munused by existing code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **treeck.c**  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduced a standalone function `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that:  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Guards against double-free using `node->state == STATE_FREED`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Recursively frees `edges` arrays and the node itself.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Updated `lzma_tree` to:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Build the tree via `create_tree`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Compute checksum via `compute_tree_checksum`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Call `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before returning the checksum.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Post-patch fuzz log**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The fuzzer run still aborts in `compute_tree_checksum` at line [0m[1;36m79[0m[39m reading freed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The free occurs inside `compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m82[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m90[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`free_tree`.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The newly added `free_tree` is never reached before the crash, since the crash [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappens during the recursive checksum calculation.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Further Investigation[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and address the heap-use-after-free, inspect:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **compute_tree_checksum**  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How and when it frees nodes during recursion.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether reads from node fields occur after freeing child memory.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **create_tree**  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How the tree structure is built and initialized [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode states, edge counts[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **TreeNode definition**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Layout and intended ownership semantics of `edges` and child pointers.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Interaction between hashing and freeing logic**  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether checksum computation should traverse then free, or separate those [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconcerns.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy examining the interplay of these components, one can map out the correct [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifetime for each node and avoid freeing memory prematurely or reading stale data.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Compute initial checksum from depth and value[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:  uint32_t sum = node->value * [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Traverse the child nodes if not already visited[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->state == STATE_CLEAR[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:    node->state = STATE_VISITED;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < node->edge_count; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:      TreeNode *child = node->edges[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchild[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:        sum += [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchild, depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:    node->state = STATE_HASHED;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Free the node and edges[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:  return sum;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/treeck.[0m[1;92mc:95[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m103[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m95:e[0m[39mxtern [0m[1;35mLZMA_API[0m[1;39m([0m[39muint32_t[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:[0m[1;35mlzma_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst uint8_t *buf, size_t size, uint32_t checksum[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:  unsigned long seed = [0m[1;35mhash_data[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:  TreeNode *root = [0m[1;35mcreate_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, size, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m, seed, NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:  checksum ^= [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:  return checksum;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/treeck.[0m[1;92mc:88[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m90[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Free the node and edges[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/treeck.h:[0m[1;36m24[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m34[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m:typedef struct TreeNode [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m:  uint8_t value;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m:  uint64_t block_width;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m:  uint64_t block_height;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:  uint64_t block_size;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:  size_t edge_count;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:  struct TreeNode **edges;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m:  int state;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m for checksum cycle detection[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m TreeNode;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/liblzma/check/treeck.[0m[1;92mc:93[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m103[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m95:e[0m[39mxtern [0m[1;35mLZMA_API[0m[1;39m([0m[39muint32_t[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:[0m[1;35mlzma_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst uint8_t *buf, size_t size, uint32_t checksum[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:  unsigned long seed = [0m[1;35mhash_data[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:  TreeNode *root = [0m[1;35mcreate_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, size, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m, seed, NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:  checksum ^= [0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:  return checksum;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove in-recursion deallocation from `compute_tree_checksum`:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/liblzma/check/treeck.c`, delete the two lines freeing memory inside [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`compute_tree_checksum` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., remove `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode->edges[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` just before [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturning `sum`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This preserves the checksum‐only nature of the function, prevents premature [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrees during cycle detection, and avoids any heap-use-after-free in the presence of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mback-links.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Retain and deploy the standalone `free_tree` helper:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the previously introduced `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTreeNode *node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `treeck.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mits `STATE_FREED` guard in `treeck.h`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This routine recursively walks the entire graph once, skips any node already [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `STATE_FREED`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and safely frees each node’s `edges` array and the node [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Wire `free_tree` into the public API:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `lzma_tree` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `treeck.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after computing the checksum with the now‐pure[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcompute_tree_checksum[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, call `[0m[1;35mfree_tree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before returning the final[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecksum.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures full cleanup happens exactly once, after all nodes have been [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhashed, without impacting traversal logic.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. State‐flag considerations:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Leave the new `STATE_FREED` constant in `treeck.h` so `free_tree` can detect [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand skip already‐freed nodes.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `compute_tree_checksum` continues to use `STATE_CLEAR`, `STATE_VISITED`, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`STATE_HASHED` for proper cycle‐safe traversal.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no overlap: after checksum, nodes are `STATE_HASHED`; `free_tree` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreassigns `STATE_FREED` and triggers deallocation.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification and side‐effects:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By separating traversal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchecksum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from memory‐management, we eliminate the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause of premature frees and UAFs under cycles.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This preserves existing functionality: checksum values remain identical, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall allocated memory is reclaimed exactly once.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No fuzz harness, test code, or external libraries are modified.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential memory‐leak concerns are addressed by the guaranteed `free_tree` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall in every code path of `lzma_tree`.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar separation of concerns is standard in other parts of the codebase [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcompare `lZMA_API` functions that perform work first, then free in a helper[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit tests for `lzma_tree` and fuzz tests [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz_encode_stream`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto confirm the UAF no longer occurs.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use AddressSanitizer to ensure no heap leaks or use-after-free remain in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecksum and free phases.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
